    "name": "MFA tutorial",
    "readme": "Tutorial showing how to use the Montreal Forced Aligner. It uses sample data that can be found on Zenodo. After uploading the data, the next step is to check whether there are any words that are not included in the dictionary (find OOVs). The next step is to then generate pronunciations of these words before merging them with the built-in dictionary. Finally, the phonetic transcriptions can be aligned to the individual sounds in the audio file.",
    "report": {
